						<summary>

						<p>This is a Vaṭṭeḻuttu record evidently of the time of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I</hi> like <hi rend="bold">No. 410</hi> above. It records a gift of 26 cows for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple by <hi rend="bold">Dharma-Seṭṭi</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śaḍaiyaṉ Kavayaṉ</hi> a member of the <hi rend="bold">Maṇigrāmam</hi> (guild) at••• llūr in Tenvāra-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
